This interval board was burried by an avalanche [insert questionable look on field safety protocol]. Lowman Road was closed 2/22@1700-2/23@1300 totaling 20hrs of closure time - likely that was the timing of the avalanche, but avy forecasters will have more information. There was no site of the board what so ever. The avalanche path was on the right hand side of the road, crossed the river, and came up to the pull out. The debris was flush with the snowplow piles at the pullout. In other words - the interval board had ~2m of new snow ;)
